<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-66-1062 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper addresses the major avenues for exposure to new internationalmarkets and the role of the Export Trading/Management Company in expandinginternational sales. Topics covered include: Progression from domestic-basedcompany to international venture. Four basic types of international salesopportunities. Gathering foreign market information. Export controlsand export licensing requirements for WECS. National Export Trading CompanyAct of 1982. Foreign Sales Corporation Act of 1984. Financing ExportSales. Issues of culture, currency, and time. The role of an Export Trading/ManagementCompany and international traders. Trade Mission do's and don't.</TEXT></DOC>